reviews.text: My husband says it tastes better than back home in States.  $5 for a small cup. Friendly staff.  Wifi for one hour. No seat inside. Outside has one table and chairs.

After getting my coffee wrong each time in 3 days, twice the last day, this short stubby lady staff (who was throwing cups around at customers instead of serving them with minimal decency, blabbering while serving) made the most duisgusting face at me ever, below any customer service standard imaginable. This was embarrassing. Several customers were visibly unhappy with her attitude. One poor fella had his expresso served splattered outside his cup when it was put on the serving table. You could see his frustration as he waited to complain but decided to let it go. She should be fired. I will Update this review with her name shortly.
lack of seats. too crowded. no place to rest. disappointed.
Amazing service — most friendly Starbucks staff in HK. Not much seats around the area but nice to have a coffee outside facing the pier during winter.
Very cosy and vibrant location and quiet for business meeting in the morning hours. Frequently visited by people who work in the office building above.

reviews.text:
這家飲品店到處也有 尖沙咀最少10家店吧
好像有一家會在你附近😂 一條街2間也有
要找一家可以坐的飲品不容易🤔🤔

去到的時間算是多人 但買東西的就沒有[笑哭]
看來大家也很喜歡坐在這裡休息吧

·雪梨甘菊茶 HKD$40
·凍菓漾草莓紅茶 HKD$39
·蜜桃啫喱綠茶 HKD$47

飲品也是飲開的味道 沒有太大分別了吧🤔
點了去冰的飲品果然不太冷 挻不錯🤭
有些飲品不能做熱 幸好店員做到剛好的溫度
